  "serviceNotes": {
    "engine oil": "Mfr row: W211 petrol models on the common European fixed maintenance plan specify engine oil and filter at 15,000 km or 12 months (oil-change.info and workshop summaries for W211 petrol). Rec row: 10,000 km is a conservative interval for turbocharged M271/M272 use in severe conditions.",
    "dust filter": "Mercedes-Benz dust filter (cabin filter) replacement per EU maintenance booklet (typically every 24 months and/or 30,000 km with major services).",
    "engine air filter": "Engine air filter follows Mercedes inspection mileage items (commonly 60,000 km or 48 months).",
    "brake fluid": "Mercedes-Benz specifies brake fluid replacement every 24 months; time-based only per operator manual guidance.",
    "check brake pad thickness": "Brake pad inspection at each scheduled service; 30,000 km mid-cycle reminder for high annual mileage.",
    "spark plugs": "Spark plugs for M272/M273 V6 and related petrol engines are renewed at extended intervals on EU sheets (commonly 60,000 km or 48 months—confirm for your engine code).",
    "coolant": "Long-life coolant exchange appears in Mercedes maintenance tables around 150,000 km for this generation; verify printed service booklet.",
    "automatic transmission fluid": "722.6/722.9 units are often lifetime-fill officially; ATF service near 60,000 km is a widely used preventive interval.",
    "manual transmission oil": "Manual gearbox oil typically long-life; renewal near 100,000 km is a common workshop recommendation.",
    "transfer case oil": "4MATIC models only. Preventive fluid renewal around 60,000 km when no OEM routine interval is listed.",
    "front axle differential oil": "4MATIC models only. Coordinate with transfer case maintenance.",
    "rear axle differential oil": "Preventive differential oil renewal around 60,000 km complements axle wear on AWD variants.",
    "coolant flush": "Full coolant exchange around 120,000 km restores inhibitors if the OEM long interval has not yet occurred.",
    "poly-V belt": "Accessory belt and tensioner near 100,000 km reduces risk of sudden ancillary failure.",
    "intake carbon clean": "Direct-injection petrol engines (e.g. some CGI variants) can accumulate intake valve deposits; walnut or chemical cleaning around 120,000 km restores airflow where symptoms appear."
  },
